n large\n$(L_1,L_2,L_3)$ lattices due to reduced numerical cost for 3D problems. The\nnumerical simulations for box/periodic $(L,1,1)$ lattice systems in a 3D\nrectangular \"tube\" with $L$ up to several hundred confirm the theoretical\ncomplexity bounds for the tensor-structured eigenvalue solvers in the limit of\nlarge $L$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 17 Aug 2014 17:10:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-08-19"}
